==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Catsup
<hw>Cat"sup</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably of East Indian origin, because it
was originally a kind of East Indian pickles. Cf. also Malay
<ets>k⟦ecr⟧chap</ets> fish sauce. <au>MW10</au>.]</ety> <def>A pureed
table sauce made predominantly from tomatoes, flavored with onions,
sugar, salt and spices; called also <altname>tomato ketchup</altname>.
The term is also applied to pureed sauces containing mushrooms, walnuts,
etc., being called in such cases <altname>mushroom ketchup</altname>,
<altname>walnut ketchup</altname>, etc.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>ketchup</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catchwater</ent>⟦br⟧

